query.result:
**English:**
124 As when, gathering corn or darnel, 125 the doves gathered in the pasture, 126 quiet, without showing their usual pride,
127 if something appears that frightens them, 128 suddenly they stop eating, 129 because they are assailed by a greater concern;
130 so I saw that fresh company 131 leave their song and flee towards the coast, 132 like a man who goes and does not know where he will end up;
133 and our departure was no less hasty.
